        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "Prefix code"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "Block code"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Convolutional code"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "B",
      "explanation": "Huffman coding produces prefix codes where no codeword is a prefix of another.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-5",
      "question": "In a Huffman tree, each internal node has:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "One child"
